CarAction.name: CarAction
CarAction.description: The actions taken when packets conforming or exceeding the configured CIR: pass (1), discard (2), remark IP Precedence (3), remark DSCP(4), remark Mpls Exp(5), remark (6)

RemarkType.name: RemarkType
RemarkType.description: typeIpPrec(1) typeDscp(2) typeMplsExp(3) typeVlan8021p(4) typeAtmClp(5) typeFrDe(6)

QueueBandwidthUnit.name: QueueBandwidthUnit
QueueBandwidthUnit.description: Bandwidth Unit: Absolute, Unit Kbps (1) Percent, Unit % (2), means the percentage of the reserved bandwidth besides the part configured for RTP queue. Remaining percent, Unit % (3), means the percentage of the reserved bandwidth besides the parts configured for EF and RTP queue.

LrCirUnit.name: LrCirUnit
LrCirUnit.description: CIR Unit: Absolute, Unit bps (1) Percent, Unit % (2)

hwCBQoSClassifierIndexNext.name: hwCBQoSClassifierIndexNext
hwCBQoSClassifierIndexNext.description: This object contains an appropriate value to be used for hwCBQoSClassifierIndex when creating rows in the hwCBQoSClassifierCfgInfoTable. Begin with 0.

hwCBQoSClassifierCfgInfoTable.name: hwCBQoSClassifierCfgInfoTable
hwCBQoSClassifierCfgInfoTable.description: A table of Traffic Classifier configuration information.

hwCBQoSClassifierIndex.name: hwCBQoSClassifierIndex
hwCBQoSClassifierIndex.description: Index of Traffic Classifier. Begin with 0.

hwCBQoSClassifierRuleCount.name: hwCBQoSClassifierRuleCount
hwCBQoSClassifierRuleCount.description: The count of match rules of Traffic classifier. It can be used for hwCBQoSMatchRuleIndex when creating rows in the hwCBQoSMatchRuleCfgInfoTable. Begin with 0.

hwCBQoSClassifierOperator.name: hwCBQoSClassifierOperator
hwCBQoSClassifierOperator.description: Operator of the match rules of traffic classifier. Software QoS support and,or. Hardware QoS support and.

hwCBQoSClassifierLayer.name: hwCBQoSClassifierLayer
hwCBQoSClassifierLayer.description: Configuration layer of traffic classifier. Only hardware QoS support it. -1(unavailable) is returned only when getting value from software QoS. -1(unavailable) can't be set.

hwCBQoSClassifierRowStatus.name: hwCBQoSClassifierRowStatus
hwCBQoSClassifierRowStatus.description: RowStatus. Three actions are used: active, createAndGo, destroy

hwCBQoSMatchRuleCfgInfoTable.name: hwCBQoSMatchRuleCfgInfoTable
hwCBQoSMatchRuleCfgInfoTable.description: A table of Match Rule configuration information.

hwCBQoSMatchRuleIfNot.name: hwCBQoSMatchRuleIfNot
hwCBQoSMatchRuleIfNot.description: whether the if-match rule is a Match or Match-Not statement. Software QoS support match,match-Not. Hardware QoS support match.

hwCBQoSMatchRuleType.name: hwCBQoSMatchRuleType
hwCBQoSMatchRuleType.description: Type of Match Rule. typeAny(1) typeAcl(2), typeRtpPort(3), typeProtocol(4), typeIpPrec(5), typeDscp(6), typeVlan8021p(7), typeMplsExp(8), typeSourceMac(9), typeDestinationMac(10), typeClassifier(11), typeInboundInterface(12), typeMacGroup(13), typeMatchDe(16), /* the match rule is FR DE */ typeMatchClp(17), /* the match rule is ATM CLP */ typeOutboundInterface(25) Software QoS supports any type except typeMacGroup. Hardware QoS supports typeAcl,typeDscp,typeMacGroup.

hwCBQoSMatchRuleStringValue.name: hwCBQoSMatchRuleStringValue
hwCBQoSMatchRuleStringValue.description: Value of Match Rule. SourceMAC(9): SIZE (12) HHHHHHHHHHHH for example: 010102020303 means the match rule is 'if-match source-mac 0101-0202-0303' DestinationMAC(10): SIZE (12) HHHHHHHHHHHH for example: 010102020303 means the match rule is 'if-match destination-mac 0101-0202-0303' Classifier(11): SIZE (1..31) InboundInterface(12): SIZE (1..47) typeOutboundInterface(25): SIZE (1..47) other type: Set is not permitted. Zero-length String will be returned when getting.

hwCBQoSMatchRuleIntValue1.name: hwCBQoSMatchRuleIntValue1
hwCBQoSMatchRuleIntValue1.description: Value of Match Rule. Acl(2): Software QoS: 2000~3999 Hardware Qos: 10000~42767 RtpPort(3): start-port: 2000~65535 Protocol(4): 1(Ip) IpPrec(5): value:0~7, up to 8 value can be input. The bit set to 1 of the last 8 bits of hwCBQoSMatchRuleIntValue1 is used to indicate the value 0~7. For example: 0x00000053(Binary format is 01010011) means the match rule is 'if-match ip-prec 0 1 4 6' Dscp(6): value:0~63,up to 8 value can be input. The bit set to 1 of hwCBQoSMatchRuleIntValue1 is used to indicate the value 32~63. The bit set to 1 of hwCBQoSMatchRuleIntValue2 is used to indicate the value 0~31. For example: 0x80000003 means the match rule is 'if-match dscp 32 33 63' Vlan8021p(7): value:0~7, up to 8 value can be input. The bit set to 1 of the last 8 bits of hwCBQoSMatchRuleIntValue1 is used to indicate the 8 value 0~7. For example: 0x53(Binary format is 01010011) means the match rule is 'if-match vlan 0 1 4 6' MplsExp(8): value:0~7, up to 8 value can be input. The bit set to 1 of the last 8 bits of hwCBQoSMatchRuleIntValue1 is used to indicate the 8 value 0~7. For example: 0x53(Binary format is 01010011) means the match rule is 'if-match mpls 0 1 4 6' MacGroup(13): 1~63 other type: Set is not permitted. 0xffffffff will be returned when getting.

hwCBQoSMatchRuleIntValue2.name: hwCBQoSMatchRuleIntValue2
hwCBQoSMatchRuleIntValue2.description: Value of Match Rule. RtpPort(3): end-port: 2000~65535 Dscp(6): value:0~63,up to 8 value can be input. The bit set to 1 of hwCBQoSMatchRuleIntValue1 is used to indicate the value 32~63. The bit set to 1 of hwCBQoSMatchRuleIntValue2 is used to indicate the value 0~31. for example: 0x80000003 means the match rule is 'if-match dscp 0 1 31' other type: Set is not permitted. 0xffffffff will be returned when getting.

hwCBQoSMatchRuleRowStatus.name: hwCBQoSMatchRuleRowStatus
hwCBQoSMatchRuleRowStatus.description: RowStatus for Match Rule Table. Three actions are used: active, createAndGo, destroy

hwCBQoSBehaviorIndexNext.name: hwCBQoSBehaviorIndexNext
hwCBQoSBehaviorIndexNext.description: This object contains an appropriate value to be used for hwCBQoSBehaviorIndex when creating rows in the hwCBQoSBehaviorCfgInfoTable. Begin with 0.

hwCBQoSBehaviorCfgInfoTable.name: hwCBQoSBehaviorCfgInfoTable
hwCBQoSBehaviorCfgInfoTable.description: A table of Traffic Behavior configuration information.

hwCBQoSBehaviorRowStatus.name: hwCBQoSBehaviorRowStatus
hwCBQoSBehaviorRowStatus.description: RowStatus. Three actions are used: active, createAndGo, destroy

hwCBQoSCarCfgInfoTable.name: hwCBQoSCarCfgInfoTable
hwCBQoSCarCfgInfoTable.description: A table of CAR feature configuration information.

hwCBQoSCarCir.name: hwCBQoSCarCir
hwCBQoSCarCir.description: Committed Information Rate. Unit: kbps. software QoS: 8..155000 hardware QoS: 100..10000000

hwCBQoSCarCbs.name: hwCBQoSCarCbs
hwCBQoSCarCbs.description: Committed Burst Size. Unit: byte software QoS: 1875..19375000 (default:max(cir*125/2,1875)) hardware QoS: 64..131071(default:12288)

hwCBQoSCarEbs.name: hwCBQoSCarEbs
hwCBQoSCarEbs.description: Excess Burst Size. Unit: byte. 0..19375000 Only software QoS support this node. -1 is returned only when getting value from hardware QoS. -1 can't be set.

hwCBQoSCarPir.name: hwCBQoSCarPir
hwCBQoSCarPir.description: Peak Information Rate. Unit: kbps. 100..10000000 Only hardware QoS support this node. -1 is returned only when getting value from software QoS. -1 can't be set.

hwCBQoSCarPbs.name: hwCBQoSCarPbs
hwCBQoSCarPbs.description: Peak Burst Size. Unit: byte. 64..4000000.(default:cbs when Peak Information Rate configured) Only hardware QoS support this node. -1 is returned only when getting value from software QoS. -1 can't be set.

hwCBQoSCarGreenAction.name: hwCBQoSCarGreenAction
hwCBQoSCarGreenAction.description: Green Action: pass (1) discard (2) remark IP Precedence (3) remark DSCP (4) remark MPLS EXP (5) remark (6) Hardware QoS : pass, discard, remark. Software QoS : pass, discard, remark IP Precedence, remark DSCP, remark MPLS EXP.

hwCBQoSCarGreenRemarkValue.name: hwCBQoSCarGreenRemarkValue
hwCBQoSCarGreenRemarkValue.description: The value is to remark When green action is remarking. For remarking DSCP, the range is 0~63; For remarking IP Precedence and MPLS EXP, the range is 0~7; Only software QoS support this node. -1 is returned only when getting value from hardware QoS or when action being pass, discard of software QoS. -1 can't be set.

hwCBQoSCarYellowAction.name: hwCBQoSCarYellowAction
hwCBQoSCarYellowAction.description: Yellow Action: unavailable(-1) pass (1) discard (2) remark IP Precedence (3) remark DSCP (4) remark MPLS EXP (5) remark(6) Only hardware QoS support this node. Hardware QoS support pass, discard, remark. -1 is returned only when getting value from software QoS. -1 can't be set.

hwCBQoSCarRedAction.name: hwCBQoSCarRedAction
hwCBQoSCarRedAction.description: Red Action: pass (1) discard (2) remark IP Precedence (3) remark DSCP (4) remark MPLS EXP (5) remark (6) Hardware QoS : pass, discard, remark. Software QoS : pass, discard, remark IP Precedence, remark DSCP, remark MPLS EXP.

hwCBQoSCarRedRemarkValue.name: hwCBQoSCarRedRemarkValue
hwCBQoSCarRedRemarkValue.description: The value is to remark When red action is remarking. For remarking DSCP, the range is 0~63; For remarking IP Precedence and MPLS EXP, the range is 0~7; Only software QoS support this node. -1 is returned only when getting value from hardware QoS or when action being pass, discard of software QoS. -1 can't be set.

hwCBQoSCarRowStatus.name: hwCBQoSCarRowStatus
hwCBQoSCarRowStatus.description: RowStatus. Three actions are used: active, createAndGo, destroy

hwCBQoSGtsCfgInfoTable.name: hwCBQoSGtsCfgInfoTable
hwCBQoSGtsCfgInfoTable.description: A table of GTS feature configuration information.

hwCBQoSGtsCbs.name: hwCBQoSGtsCbs
hwCBQoSGtsCbs.description: Committed Burst Size. Unit: bit default: max(cir*1/2,15000)

hwCBQoSGtsRowStatus.name: hwCBQoSGtsRowStatus
hwCBQoSGtsRowStatus.description: RowStatus. Three actions are used: active, createAndGo, destroy

hwCBQoSRemarkCfgInfoTable.name: hwCBQoSRemarkCfgInfoTable
hwCBQoSRemarkCfgInfoTable.description: A table of Remarking feature configuration information.

hwCBQoSRemarkType.name: hwCBQoSRemarkType
hwCBQoSRemarkType.description: IpPrec(1) Dscp(2) MplsExp(3) Vlan8021p(4) AtmClp(5) FrDe(6) Hardware QoS support IpPrec, Dscp,MplsExp, Vlan8021p. Software QoS support each type.

hwCBQoSRemarkValue.name: hwCBQoSRemarkValue
hwCBQoSRemarkValue.description: Value to remark: for IpPrec: 0~7; for Dscp: 0~63; for Vlan8021p: 0~7; for AtmClp: 0~1; for FrDe: 0~1; for MplsExp: 0~7

hwCBQoSRemarkRowStatus.name: hwCBQoSRemarkRowStatus
hwCBQoSRemarkRowStatus.description: RowStatus. Three actions are used: active, createAndGo, destroy

hwCBQoSQueueCfgInfoTable.name: hwCBQoSQueueCfgInfoTable
hwCBQoSQueueCfgInfoTable.description: A table of queueing feature configuration information.

hwCBQoSQueueDropType.name: hwCBQoSQueueDropType
hwCBQoSQueueDropType.description: The drop type of queue. Only valid for AF and WFQ queue. -1 is returned only when getting value about EF queue. -1 can't be set.

hwCBQoSQueueLength.name: hwCBQoSQueueLength
hwCBQoSQueueLength.description: The length of QueueLength. Only valid for tail-drop type of AF and WFQ queue. -1 is returned only when getting value about EF queue or wred type of AF and WFQ queue. -1 can't be set.

hwCBQoSQueueBandwidthUnit.name: hwCBQoSQueueBandwidthUnit
hwCBQoSQueueBandwidthUnit.description: Bandwidth Unit: Absolute, Unit Kbps (1) Percent, Unit % (2) Remaining percent, Unit % (3) Absolute unit and percent unit are valid for EF and AF queue, but remaining percent unit is only valid for AF queue. -1 is returned only when getting value about WFQ queue. -1 can't be set.

hwCBQoSQueueBandwidthValue.name: hwCBQoSQueueBandwidthValue
hwCBQoSQueueBandwidthValue.description: Bandwidth value: Absolute value: 8~1000000. Unit: Kbps Percent value: 1~100. Remaining percent value: 1~100. Absolute value and percent value are valid for EF and AF queue, but remaining percent value is only valid for AF queue. -1 is returned only when getting value about WFQ queue. -1 can't be set.

hwCBQoSQueueCbs.name: hwCBQoSQueueCbs
hwCBQoSQueueCbs.description: Committed Burst Size. Unit: byte. Only valid for EF queue. Default:min( Bandwidth*25 , 2000000) -1 is returned only when getting value about AF or WFQ queue. -1 can't be set.

hwCBQoSQueueQueueNumber.name: hwCBQoSQueueQueueNumber
hwCBQoSQueueQueueNumber.description: Max number of hashed queues (a power of 2). Only valid for WFQ. -1 is returned only when getting value about AF or EF queue. -1 can't be set.

hwCBQoSQueueRowStatus.name: hwCBQoSQueueRowStatus
hwCBQoSQueueRowStatus.description: RowStatus. Three actions are used: active, createAndGo, destroy

hwCBQoSQueueCbsRatio.name: hwCBQoSQueueCbsRatio
hwCBQoSQueueCbsRatio.description: Committed Burst Size Ratio. Unit: byte. CBS = CBS_Ratio * Bandwidth(kbps) Only valid for EF queue. -1 is returned only when getting value about AF or WFQ queue. -1 can't be set.

hwCBQoSWredCfgInfoTable.name: hwCBQoSWredCfgInfoTable
hwCBQoSWredCfgInfoTable.description: A table of WRED configuration information.

hwCBQoSWredWeightConst.name: hwCBQoSWredWeightConst
hwCBQoSWredWeightConst.description: Specify weight for calculating mean queue depth.

hwCBQoSWredClassCfgInfoTable.name: hwCBQoSWredClassCfgInfoTable
hwCBQoSWredClassCfgInfoTable.description: A table of WRED configuration information.

hwCBQoSWredClassValue.name: hwCBQoSWredClassValue
hwCBQoSWredClassValue.description: The class value. For IP precedence based WRED, the class is IP precedence, and range is 0~7. For DSCP based WRED, the class is DSCP, and range is 0~63.

hwCBQoSWredClassLowLimit.name: hwCBQoSWredClassLowLimit
hwCBQoSWredClassLowLimit.description: The low limit of queue depth.

hwCBQoSWredClassHighLimit.name: hwCBQoSWredClassHighLimit
hwCBQoSWredClassHighLimit.description: The high limit of queue depth.

hwCBQoSPolicyRouteCfgInfoTable.name: hwCBQoSPolicyRouteCfgInfoTable
hwCBQoSPolicyRouteCfgInfoTable.description: A table of Policy Routeing configuration information.

hwCBQoSPolicyRouteNexthop.name: hwCBQoSPolicyRouteNexthop
hwCBQoSPolicyRouteNexthop.description: The next-hop ip address for redirection

hwCBQoSPolicyRouteBackup.name: hwCBQoSPolicyRouteBackup
hwCBQoSPolicyRouteBackup.description: Whether forward the packet according to the routing table When the next-hop ip address for redirection is not valid. Backup means forwarding. NoBackup means not forwarding

hwCBQoSPolicyRouteRowStatus.name: hwCBQoSPolicyRouteRowStatus
hwCBQoSPolicyRouteRowStatus.description: RowStatus. Three actions are used: active, createAndGo, destroy

hwCBQoSNatCfgInfoTable.description: A table of Nat configuration information.

hwCBQoSFirewallCfgInfoTable.description: A table of Firewall configuration information.

hwCBQoSSamplingRowStatus.description: RowStatus. Three actions are used: active, createAndGo, destroy

hwCBQoSLrCfgInfoTable.name: hwCBQoSLrCfgInfoTable
hwCBQoSLrCfgInfoTable.description: A table of Line Rate configuration information.

hwCBQoSLrUnit.name: hwCBQoSLrUnit
hwCBQoSLrUnit.description: CIR Unit: Absolute, Unit bps (1) Percent, Unit % (2)

hwCBQoSLrCir.name: hwCBQoSLrCir
hwCBQoSLrCir.description: Committed Information Rate. Absolute value: 8000..1000000000. Unit: bps Percent value: 1~100.

hwCBQoSLrCbs.name: hwCBQoSLrCbs
hwCBQoSLrCbs.description: Committed Burst Size. When CIR is absolute value, CBS value: 15000..1000000000, default value: max(cir*1/2,15000), Unit: bit; When CIR is percent value, CBS value: 50..2000, default value: 500, Unit: ms.

hwCBQoSLrEbs.name: hwCBQoSLrEbs
hwCBQoSLrEbs.description: Excess Burst Size. When CIR is absolute value, EBS value: 0..1000000000, Unit: bit; When CIR is percent value, EBS value: 0..2000, Unit: ms.

hwCBQoSLrRowStatus.name: hwCBQoSLrRowStatus
hwCBQoSLrRowStatus.description: RowStatus. Three actions are used: active, createAndGo, destroy

hwCBQoSPolicyClassIndex.name: hwCBQoSPolicyClassIndex
hwCBQoSPolicyClassIndex.description: PolicyClass Index in a QoS policy.

hwCBQoSPolicyClassClassifierIndex.name: hwCBQoSPolicyClassClassifierIndex
hwCBQoSPolicyClassClassifierIndex.description: Index of classifier applied by a policy. It should exist in hwCBQoSClassifierCfgInfoTable.

hwCBQoSPolicyClassRowStatus.name: hwCBQoSPolicyClassRowStatus
hwCBQoSPolicyClassRowStatus.description: RowStatus. Three actions are used: active, createAndGo, destroy

hwCBQoSIfApplyPolicyEnableDynamic.description: If the value of it is specified 'true', enable dynamic qos policy. -1(unavailable) is returned if device doesn't support dynamic QoS. -1(unavailable) can't be set.

hwCBQoSIfApplyPolicyRowStatus.name: hwCBQoSIfApplyPolicyRowStatus
hwCBQoSIfApplyPolicyRowStatus.description: RowStatus. Three actions are used: active, createAndGo, destroy

hwCBQoSAtmPvcApplyPolicyEntry.name: hwCBQoSAtmPvcApplyPolicyEntry
hwCBQoSAtmPvcApplyPolicyEntry.description: Policy applied on ATM PVC Configuration Information Entry.
